   "body" : "Occasionally sending a transaction will result in a comically expensive amount of inputs being spent. Often this is totally unexpected, and the sender would have preferred to have instead have fallen back onto a different selection with less inputs or failing that have not make the transaction (until after they do some consolidation).\r\n\r\nI propose there is an option \"-maxInputs\" that can be set by senders to force coin selection to never spend more that inputs.",
